    "message_1": "Solve the following system of linear equations using the Jacobi iterative method:\n$$\n\\begin{matrix}\n4x_1 + x_2 + 2x_3 & = & 4\\\\\nx_1 + 4x_2 + x_3 & = & 1\\\\\n2x_1 + x_2 + 5x_3 & = & -1\n\\end{matrix}\n$$\nStarting from the initial guess $(x_1^{(0)}, x_2^{(0)},x_3^{(0)}) = (0,0,0)$, use 5 iterations to obtain the solution accurate to 3 decimal places.",
    "message_2": "To apply the Jacobi iterative method, we first rewrite the given system of linear equations as follows:\n\n$$\nx_1 = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - x_2 - 2x_3) \\\\\nx_2 = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - x_1 - x_3) \\\\\nx_3 = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 2x_1 - x_2)\n$$\n\nNow, we will perform 5 iterations starting from the initial guess $(x_1^{(0)}, x_2^{(0)}, x_3^{(0)}) = (0, 0, 0)$.\n\nIteration 1:\n$$\nx_1^{(1)} = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - 0 - 0) = 1 \\\\\nx_2^{(1)} = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - 0 - 0) = 0.25 \\\\\nx_3^{(1)} = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 0 - 0) = -0.2\n$$\n\nIteration 2:\n$$\nx_1^{(2)} = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - 0.25 - 2(-0.2)) = 0.975 \\\\\nx_2^{(2)} = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - 1 - (-0.2)) = 0.05 \\\\\nx_3^{(2)} = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 2(1) - 0.25) = -0.55\n$$\n\nIteration 3:\n$$\nx_1^{(3)} = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - 0.05 - 2(-0.55)) = 0.9875 \\\\\nx_2^{(3)} = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - 0.975 - (-0.55)) = 0.144 \\\\\nx_3^{(3)} = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 2(0.975) - 0.05) = -0.49\n$$\n\nIteration 4:\n$$\nx_1^{(4)} = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - 0.144 - 2(-0.49)) = 1.016 \\\\\nx_2^{(4)} = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - 0.9875 - (-0.49)) = 0.126 \\\\\nx_3^{(4)} = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 2(1.016) - 0.144) = -0.532\n$$\n\nIteration 5:\n$$\nx_1^{(5)} = \\frac{1}{4}(4 - 0.126 - 2(-0.532)) = 1.003 \\\\\nx_2^{(5)} = \\frac{1}{4}(1 - 1.016 - (-0.532)) = 0.129 \\\\\nx_3^{(5)} = \\frac{1}{5}(-1 - 2(1.003) - 0.126) = -0.526\n$$\n\nAfter 5 iterations, the solution accurate to 3 decimal places is $(x_1, x_2, x_3) = (1.003, 0.129, -0.526)$."
